'''Bobby Clark''' (born November 13, 1944 in Seattle) is an American film, TV and stage actor.
Probably his longest lasting role was Casey Junior in ''[[Casey Jones (TV series)]]''.
He appeared in the original movies "Invasion of the Body Snatchers", "Ransom", "Gun Duel in Durango", "Rebel in Town", "The Happy Road", "Bring Your Smile Along", "The Ten Commandments"
He also appeared in episodes of "Perry Mason", "Alfred Hitchcock Presents", "The Loretta Young Show", "The Jimmy Durante Show", "The Americans", "Lassie", "GE Theatre", "Ford Theatre", "Studio 57", "PepsiCola Playhouse", "Screen Directors Playhouse", "Climax", "Front Row Center", "Zane Grey Theatre", "Northwest Passage", "Crossroads", "Bachelor Father"
His parents were Robert Boyd Clark and Jean Dahl Clark. He began his professional career at the age of six when he was introduced to the accordian. He played many public events including USO shows, professional wrestling matches and all local service clubs including Kiwanis and Elk Clubs. In 1954 he moved with his parents to Los Angeles. In addition to his movie and television appearances, he performed at the Hollywood Bowl and at local festivals and events.
